  <li><strong>The Color Code Reveals Everything</strong> - When selecting rosé, use color intensity as your quality compass. Pale salmon indicates saignée method (juice bled off from red wine tanks), delivering more structure and complexity. Bright pink suggests direct pressing, yielding fresher, more delicate wines. Deep copper-rose signals extended skin contact or warmer climates, producing fuller-bodied styles perfect for heartier dishes.</li>

