  <li><strong>Skip the Decanter, Embrace the Chill</strong> - Unlike reds, rosé never benefits from decanting. The style relies on freshness and primary fruit aromatics that dissipate with excessive air exposure. Instead, keep bottles in ice buckets throughout service. The only exception: vintage Champagne rosé over 10 years old may benefit from 15 minutes of gentle aeration.</li>

