  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the difference between Provence rosé and New World rosé styles?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Provence rosé typically exhibits pale salmon colors with delicate mineral-driven flavors of white peach, herbs, and citrus, achieved through minimal skin contact and cool fermentation. New World rosés from regions like California or Australia tend to be more fruit-forward with deeper pink hues, showing flavors of strawberry, watermelon, and tropical fruits. The key difference lies in winemaking philosophy: Provence emphasizes restraint and terroir expression, while New World producers often prioritize bold fruit character and accessibility.</p>
