    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">How do I choose rosé wine for different food pairings?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Lighter, drier rosés with high acidity (like Sancerre rosé or Provence styles) pair beautifully with seafood, salads, and Mediterranean cuisine. Medium-bodied rosés from Rhône varieties work well with grilled chicken, pork, and Asian fusion dishes. For richer foods like barbecue or spicy cuisine, choose fuller-bodied rosés with more residual sugar, such as White Zinfandel or off-dry rosé from Languedoc.</p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">Should rosé wine be served immediately after opening or can it benefit from decanting?</h3>
