  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">How long can opened rosé wine last in the refrigerator?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Opened rosé wine typically maintains its best quality for 3-5 days when properly stored in the refrigerator with a wine stopper or vacuum pump to minimize oxygen exposure. The high acidity in most rosés helps preserve freshness longer than many white wines, but the delicate fruit flavors will start to fade after the first few days. For optimal enjoyment, consume opened rosé within 2-3 days, as the vibrant aromatics and crisp finish that define quality rosé diminish with extended exposure to air.</p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibred text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the best value alternative to expensive Provence rosé?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Languedoc rosé offers exceptional value with similar Provençal style at 30-50% less cost, featuring the same Mediterranean grape varieties and winemaking techniques. Spanish Rosado from Navarra and Rioja provides another excellent alternative with crisp minerality and food-friendly acidity. For those seeking the pale, elegant style of premium Provence, look for rosés from Côtes du Rhône or Ventoux appellations, which deliver comparable quality and terroir expression at more accessible price points.</p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">Can rosé wine age well, or should it always be consumed young?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">While most rosé wines are crafted for immediate consumption within 1-2 years of vintage, premium rosés from top Provence producers like Domaine de la Croix or Château Minuty can develop beautifully for 3-5 years. These age-worthy rosés typically show more concentration, complexity, and structure from extended lees contact and careful vineyard selection. However, the fresh fruit character that defines rosé style will evolve into more honeyed, nutty notes with age, so personal preference determines whether this development is desirable.</p>
